@startuml
title Sending a Message with Media Attachment

actor "User" as User
participant "Main Content Widget" as MCW
participant "API Facade" as API
participant "Task Queue" as TQ
participant "File Preparation Task" as FPT
participant "Upload Manager" as UM
participant "Histories Registry" as HR
participant "History" as H
participant "Data Model" as DM
participant "Protocol Engine" as PE
participant "Telegram Server" as TS
participant "Update Dispatcher" as UD
participant "Change Notifier" as CN

== File Selection and Preparation ==

User -> MCW : select file and confirm send
MCW -> API : send-files operation\n(file, peer context, message options)
API -> TQ : enqueue File Preparation Task

activate TQ
TQ -> FPT : run on worker thread
activate FPT
FPT -> FPT : read file bytes
FPT -> FPT : generate thumbnails
FPT -> FPT : compute metadata and file identifier
FPT --> TQ : upload-ready descriptor
deactivate FPT
TQ --> API : preparation complete
deactivate TQ

== Local Message Creation ==

API -> DM : register random-identifier to local message identifier mapping
API -> H : create Message Item\n(local id, random id, status: sending)
H -> CN : publish message add event
CN --> MCW : local message appears in History view

note right of H
  Message is visible immediately
  before upload completes.
end note

== Parallel Upload ==

API -> UM : upload descriptor
activate UM
UM -> UM : split file into parts

loop for each part group (parallel)
    UM -> PE : upload part\n(shifted upload data-centre identifier)
    activate PE
    PE -> TS : part data
    TS --> PE : part acknowledgement
    PE --> UM : part confirmed
    deactivate PE
    UM -> H : update upload progress on Message Item
end

alt upload part fails
    UM -> UM : retry part upload
    alt persistent failure
        UM --> API : upload failed
        API -> H : mark Message Item as failed
        H -> CN : publish message change event
        CN --> MCW : History view refreshes (failed state)
    end
end

UM --> API : document-ready or photo-ready event
deactivate UM

== Send-Media Request Construction ==

API -> API : build input media\n(uploaded file reference)
API -> API : apply message flags\n(reply, silent, scheduled, send-as, effect)

alt per-peer send restrictions or slow-mode active
    API -> API : check send restrictions for peer
    API --> MCW : block send, show restriction notice
end

alt paid-message stars required
    API --> MCW : prompt stars approval
    User -> MCW : confirm stars payment
end

== Request Dispatch ==

API -> HR : send prepared message\n(peer, input media, flags)
activate HR
HR -> HR : queue request per History
HR -> PE : dispatch send-media request
activate PE
PE -> TS : send-media request
TS --> PE : updates result
PE --> HR : updates result
deactivate PE
HR --> API : updates result
deactivate HR

alt send-media request fails
    PE --> HR : Protocol Error
    HR --> API : send failed
    API -> H : mark Message Item as failed\n(by random identifier)
    H -> CN : publish message change event
    CN --> MCW : History view refreshes (failed state)
end

== Update Application ==

API -> UD : apply updates result
activate UD
UD -> DM : resolve random identifier to server message identifier
DM -> H : replace local Message Item with server-confirmed Message Item
H -> CN : publish message and history change events
deactivate UD
CN --> MCW : History view refreshes (confirmed state)

== Album Edge Case ==

note over API, UM
  Multiple files form an album.
  Parts for each file upload independently and in parallel.
  The send-media album request is dispatched
  only after all album items are ready.
end note

== Cancel or Pause Edge Case ==

note over User, UM
  The User may pause or cancel an upload per message identifier.
  Cancellation removes the local Message Item from the History.
end note

@enduml
